        "method": "POST",
        "url": "http://vibe-kanban.sisyphus.svc.cluster.local:3005/execute",
        "sendBody": true,
        "contentType": "json",
        "specifyBody": "keypair",
        "options": {
          "timeout": 120000
        },
        "bodyParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "prompt",
              "value": "=You have access to vibe-kanban MCP tools and standard Bash/Read/Edit tools.\n\nTask: Set up an isolated vibe-kanban workspace for feature \"{{ $node[\"Parse Request\"].json.req_id }}\".\n\nSteps:\n1. Use the vibe-kanban MCP tool `start_workspace` to create a workspace for repo \"ttpos-server-go\" with base branch \"main\" and name \"{{ $node[\"Parse Request\"].json.req_id }}\".\n2. Use the vibe-kanban MCP tool `get_repo` to confirm the repo path for \"ttpos-server-go\".\n3. Use Bash to find the actual worktree path: run `git -C /projects/ttpos-server-go worktree list` and extract the line matching the workspace branch.\n4. Save a design contract to `/data/contracts/{{ $node[\"Parse Request\"].json.req_id }}.md` containing: req_id, title, description, workspace branch, and worktree path.\n\nAt the very end of your response, output EXACTLY this JSON block and nothing else after it:\nFINAL_JSON:\n{\n  \"workspace_id\": \"<workspace_uuid>\",\n  \"branch\": \"<workspace_branch>\",\n  \"worktree_path\": \"<absolute_worktree_path>\",\n  \"status\": \"success\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "cwd",
              "value": "/projects/ttpos-server-go"
            },
            {
              "name": "timeout",
              "value": 120000
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "p0-parse",
      "name": "P0: Parse Output",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        650,
        600
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const data = $input.first().json;\nconst out = data.output || '';\nlet parsed = {};\ntry {\n  const m = out.match(/FINAL_JSON:\\s*({[\\s\\S]*})/);\n  if (m) parsed = JSON.parse(m[1]);\n} catch(e) {}\nreturn [{ json: { ...data, ...parsed } }];"
      }
    },
